31. Twas the night before Christmas and all through the Realm, Not an arrow was stirring, nor Dovahkiin's helm. Dragons flew in the sky, screaming with joy, The Jarls were tucked in, dreaming of toys. I lay in my bed, of my house in Solitude Hold, As the air danced, spreading snow though the cold. I was fading away, into a deep slumber, When I heard a sound, just like cracked lumber I sprang from my bed to see what’s the matter And looked from my window as the noise continued to clatter From up in my house, I saw quite a sight, A red suited man, flying through the night. He sat on a sleigh, pulled by nine deer, All of them looked to be a fine looking steer. I ran out' my room, and flew down the stairs To the door, as I pulled on my winter wears. I ran to the streets as the fat red man flew Across the night sky, tinted dark blue I shouted to him, "Hey who are you?" But on the man went, he flew, flew and flew Across all the forests, maintains, and slews. I watched for a moment as he disappeared from the sky, And I wondered, 'who in the hell was that guy?' I walked back inside, as the cold shot though my limbs And realized, it was Santa, bringing Christmas to Skyrim! Merry Christmas and Happy Holidays to all! https://www.reddit.com/r/skyrim/comments/1sqsbx/fus_ro_dah_merry_christmas/
